<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="28" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<paragraph blockId="3.[265,1368,204,286]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
1 Scutellum laterally setulose, dorsally glossy without pubescence; intermediate scutellar bristle much shorter than basal scutellar bristle; wing markings as in 
<figureCitation box="[658,734,262,286]" captionStart="Figures 52, 53" captionStartId="28.[204,275,1222,1244]" captionTargetBox="[206,1338,208,1196]" captionTargetId="figure-9@28.[204,1338,198,1196]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Figures 52, 53.(52) Bama papuanum (Hennig), distal part of aedeagus.Scale = 0.2 mm.(53) BamashinonagaiMcAlpine, left wing of holotype, male.bu, bulb;g, glans;lg, distal lobe of glans;pg, lobe of preglans;st, stipe;tf, terminal filaments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684920" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684920/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
......................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="McAlpine" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2001" box="[1135,1368,262,286]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shinonagai">
<emphasis box="[1135,1254,262,286]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">shinonagai</emphasis>
McAlpine
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[265,1368,300,382]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="27">—— Scutellum without setulae, its dorsal surface with covering of minute erect pubescence; intermediate scutellar bristle c. as long as basal scutellar bristle; wing markings otherwise .................................................................. 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<paragraph blockId="3.[265,1368,414,497]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
2 Marginal and submarginal cells of wing entirely dark brown to black, or (in male) first posterior cell with spotted pattern (
<figureCitation box="[363,441,473,497]" captionStart="Figures 23–26" captionStartId="16.[357,429,1683,1705]" captionTargetBox="[357,1186,151,1657]" captionTargetId="figure-9@16.[357,1186,151,1668]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figures 23–26. Bama gressitti n.sp. (23) Left wing of male. (24) Left wing of female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684893/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
) ..................................................................................................................................... 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[265,1368,510,564]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="27">—— Marginal and submarginal cells with hyaline to pale yellowish zones; first posterior cell without such pattern .......................................................................... 5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<paragraph blockId="3.[265,1368,595,678]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
3 Vein 5 on distal part of discal cell surrounded by pale brown zone; discal crossvein almost straight; palpus dark grey-brown; 
<specimenCount box="[355,375,655,678]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
only: first posterior cell with complex spotted pattern (
<figureCitation box="[942,1016,654,678]" captionStart="Figures 23–26" captionStartId="16.[357,429,1683,1705]" captionTargetBox="[357,1186,151,1657]" captionTargetId="figure-9@16.[357,1186,151,1668]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figures 23–26. Bama gressitti n.sp. (23) Left wing of male. (24) Left wing of female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684893/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
) ............................ 
<taxonomicName authority="McAlpine, 2015" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[1225,1311,655,678]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gressitti" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis box="[1225,1311,655,678]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">gressitti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1318,1368,655,678]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[265,1368,691,774]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
—— Vein 5 on discal cell not clouded with brown; discal crossvein curved; palpus variable in colour; 
<specimenCount box="[734,754,721,744]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
only: first posterior cell without spotted pattern (so far as known) ................................................................................. 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<paragraph blockId="3.[265,1368,806,918]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
4 Vein 2 with abrupt flexure just before level of anterior crossvein (
<figureCitation box="[363,426,836,860]" captionStart="Figures 7–10" captionStartId="9.[166,238,1172,1194]" captionTargetBox="[167,1466,211,1127]" captionTargetId="figure-9@9.[167,1467,201,1157]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figures 7–10. Bama flexifer n.sp., holotype male. (7) Head. (8) Left wing. (9) Distal part of aedeagus, scale = 0.3 mm. (10) Right arista (basal segmentation unclear).bu, bulb;fs, flexible section of aedeagus; g, glans; lg, distal lobe of glans;pg, preglans;tf, terminal filaments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684877" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684877/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
); dark mark enclosing discal crossvein broadly confluent with dark costal zone; prescutellar acrostichal bristle present; arista uniformly short-haired, with simple apex (
<figureCitation box="[872,949,894,918]" captionStart="Figures 7–10" captionStartId="9.[166,238,1172,1194]" captionTargetBox="[167,1466,211,1127]" captionTargetId="figure-9@9.[167,1467,201,1157]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figures 7–10. Bama flexifer n.sp., holotype male. (7) Head. (8) Left wing. (9) Distal part of aedeagus, scale = 0.3 mm. (10) Right arista (basal segmentation unclear).bu, bulb;fs, flexible section of aedeagus; g, glans; lg, distal lobe of glans;pg, preglans;tf, terminal filaments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684877" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684877/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) ....................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="McAlpine, 2015" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[1237,1311,894,918]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flexifer" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis box="[1237,1311,894,918]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">flexifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1318,1368,895,918]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[265,1368,932,1044]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
—— Vein 2 with moderate curvature only (
<figureCitation box="[755,833,932,956]" captionStart="Figures 17–20" captionStartId="13.[166,238,1744,1766]" captionTargetBox="[186,1444,160,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-9@13.[166,1466,151,1729]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figures 17–20. Bama signifer n.sp., holotype female. (17) Left wing. (18) Right mid coxa, anteroventral view. (19) Distal half of left arista, scale = 0.2 mm. (20) Dorsal view of abdomen, sclerites outlined only." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684887" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684887/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
); discal crossvein not enclosed in brown mark; prescutellar acrostichal bristle absent; arista bare on most of length, with lanceolate subapical palette (at least in female; 
<figureCitation box="[637,713,1020,1044]" captionStart="Figures 17–20" captionStartId="13.[166,238,1744,1766]" captionTargetBox="[186,1444,160,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-9@13.[166,1466,151,1729]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figures 17–20. Bama signifer n.sp., holotype female. (17) Left wing. (18) Right mid coxa, anteroventral view. (19) Distal half of left arista, scale = 0.2 mm. (20) Dorsal view of abdomen, sclerites outlined only." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684887" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684887/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
) ......................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="McAlpine, 2015" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[1230,1311,1020,1044]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="signifer" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis box="[1230,1311,1020,1044]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">signifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1318,1368,1020,1043]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<paragraph blockId="3.[265,1368,1075,1188]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
5 Anal crossvein subangularly bent near mid-length; wing markings approximately as in 
<figureCitation box="[682,745,1105,1129]" captionStart="Figures 1, 2" captionStartId="5.[249,321,990,1012]" captionTargetBox="[249,1366,168,970]" captionTargetId="figure-260@5.[249,1383,149,982]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 1, 2. Bama bipunctatum (Hendel). (1) Left wing of male, Sirinumu Dam. (2) Distal part of aedeagus, Sirinumu Dam, scale = 0.1 mm.bu, bulb; fs, flexible section of aedeagus; g, glans;lg, distal lobe of glans;pg, preglans;tf, terminal filaments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684867" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684867/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
, but sometimes stigmatal brown band fading posteriorly; fore femur entirely brown; hind femur yellow ............................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hendel)" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" box="[1133,1368,1164,1188]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipunctatum">
<emphasis box="[1133,1266,1164,1188]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">bipunctatum</emphasis>
(Hendel)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[265,1368,1201,1254]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="27">—— Anal crossvein most strongly bent or curved on anterior part; wing markings diverse; coloration of femora diverse ............................................................... 6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<paragraph blockId="3.[265,1368,1286,1369]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="27">6 Capitellum of halter dark brown to black; apical part of first posterior cell largely hyaline, but with very narrow apical marginal brown line .................................................................................................................. 7</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[265,1368,1382,1436]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="27">—— Capitellum of halter white or yellow; apical part of first posterior cell variable, but often partly brown .......................................................................... 8</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<paragraph blockId="3.[265,1368,1468,1521]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
7 Distal parts of veins 3 and 4 almost straight, markedly diverging to apex; wing markings as in 
<figureCitation box="[669,731,1497,1521]" captionStart="Figures 3, 4" captionStartId="6.[352,424,1977,1999]" captionTargetBox="[204,1338,1276,1961]" captionTargetId="figure-603@6.[204,1338,1276,1961]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figures 3, 4. Bama divergens n.sp., male. (3) Left wing. (4) Right hind tibia and tarsus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684871" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684871/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
(male) ......................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="McAlpine, 2015" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[1207,1311,1497,1521]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="divergens" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis box="[1207,1311,1497,1521]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">divergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1318,1368,1497,1520]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[265,1368,1534,1588]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
—— Distal parts of veins 3 and 4 curved, not divergent; wing markings as in 
<figureCitation box="[463,525,1563,1588]" captionStart="Figures 5, 6" captionStartId="8.[320,392,1299,1321]" captionTargetBox="[204,1338,143,1290]" captionTargetId="figure-10@8.[204,1338,136,1290]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 5, 6. Bama robertsi n.sp., holotype female. (5) Right wing. (6) Abdomen, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684873" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684873/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
(female) ........................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="McAlpine, 2015" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[1227,1311,1564,1588]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robertsi" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis box="[1227,1311,1564,1588]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">robertsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1318,1368,1564,1587]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<paragraph blockId="3.[265,1368,1620,1732]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
8 Hind basitarsus less than one third length of hind tibia (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 11–13" captionStartId="10.[355,427,1491,1513]" captionTargetBox="[204,1338,151,1475]" captionTargetId="figure-129@10.[204,1338,151,1475]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figures 11–13. Bama brevitarse n.sp., holotype male. (11) Right wing. (12) Right hind" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684881" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684881/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
); discal crossvein curved, but not with general oblique orientation; brown wing markings diffuse and irregular (at least in male, 
<figureCitation box="[448,524,1708,1732]" captionStart="Figures 11–13" captionStartId="10.[355,427,1491,1513]" captionTargetBox="[204,1338,151,1475]" captionTargetId="figure-129@10.[204,1338,151,1475]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figures 11–13. Bama brevitarse n.sp., holotype male. (11) Right wing. (12) Right hind" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684881" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684881/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) ................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="McAlpine, 2015" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[1203,1311,1708,1732]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevitarse" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis box="[1203,1311,1708,1732]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">brevitarse</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1318,1368,1708,1731]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[265,1368,1745,1828]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="27">—— Hind basitarsus more than one third length of hind tibia; discal crossvein usually with general oblique orientation, despite curvature; wing markings variable, but not as above ................................................................ 9</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<paragraph blockId="3.[265,1368,1860,1884]" box="[265,1368,1860,1884]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead box="[265,1368,1860,1884]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyStep box="[265,1368,1860,1884]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">9 Scutellum tawny-orange .......................................................................................................... 10</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[265,1368,1897,1921]" lastBlockId="4.[219,1323,151,330]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="28" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead box="[265,1368,1897,1921]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">—— Scutellum black or brown-black .............................................................................................. 12</keyLead>
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
<keyStep pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
10 Mid coxa with distomedial brush of very dense black setulae (
<figureCitation box="[320,397,181,205]" captionStart="Figures 39–41" captionStartId="23.[297,369,1593,1615]" captionTargetBox="[298,1328,148,1581]" captionTargetId="figure-138@23.[298,1335,136,1584]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Figures 39–41. Bama aurantium n.sp. (39) Wing of female (Stony Logging Area).(40) Mid coxae, male.(41) Distal part of aedeagus (Upper Manki), scale = 0.2 mm.bu, bulb; fs, flexible section of aedeagus; g, glans; lg," figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684909/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
); posteroventral angle of sternopleuron (katepisternum) with only very fine pale setulae .......................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="McAlpine, 2015" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[1155,1266,211,234]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurantium" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis box="[1155,1266,211,234]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">aurantium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1272,1323,211,234]" pageId="4" pageNumber="28" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[219,1323,151,330]" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
—— Mid coxa without such brush of dense, coarse, black setulae (
<figureCitation box="[317,401,277,301]" captionStart="Figures 33, 34" captionStartId="20.[356,428,1192,1214]" captionTargetBox="[231,1337,151,1179]" captionTargetId="figure-9@20.[204,1338,151,1179]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figures 33, 34. Bama grande n.sp., holotype female. (33) Right wing. (34) Mid coxae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684901" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684901/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">Figs 34</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[413,443,277,301]" captionStart="Figures 37, 38" captionStartId="22.[259,331,1610,1632]" captionTargetBox="[259,1283,151,1601]" captionTargetId="figure-189@22.[259,1283,151,1601]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figures 37, 38. Bama martini n.sp., holotype female. (37) First costal cell and adjacent region of left wing," figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684907" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684907/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">38</figureCitation>
); posteroventral angle of sternopleuron (near mid coxa) with some black setulae ................................................................................................. 11
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<keyStep pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
<paragraph blockId="4.[219,1323,362,474]" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
11 Dark brown stripe enclosing both anterior and discal crossveins (
<figureCitation box="[316,442,391,415]" captionStart="Figures 35, 36" captionStartId="21.[370,442,1409,1431]" captionTargetBox="[251,1369,164,1393]" captionTargetId="figure-10@21.[249,1383,151,1393]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figures 35, 36. Bama martini n.sp., (35) Right wing of holotype, female. (36) Paratype male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684903" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684903/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">Figs 35, 36</figureCitation>
); base of submarginal cell brown; first costal cell extensively microtrichose; discal crossvein less than twice as long as anterior crossvein .................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="McAlpine, 2015" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[1187,1266,451,474]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martini" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis box="[1187,1266,451,474]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">martini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1272,1323,451,474]" pageId="4" pageNumber="28" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[219,1323,487,599]" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
—— Only incomplete brownish stripe on anterior and discal crossveins (
<figureCitation box="[433,509,517,541]" captionStart="Figures 33, 34" captionStartId="20.[356,428,1192,1214]" captionTargetBox="[231,1337,151,1179]" captionTargetId="figure-9@20.[204,1338,151,1179]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figures 33, 34. Bama grande n.sp., holotype female. (33) Right wing. (34) Mid coxae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684901" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684901/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
); base of submarginal cell hyaline; first costal cell bare except near distal extremity; discal crossvein more than twice as long as anterior crossvein .................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="McAlpine, 2015" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[1190,1266,575,599]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grande" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis box="[1190,1266,575,599]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">grande</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1272,1323,576,599]" pageId="4" pageNumber="28" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
<paragraph blockId="4.[219,1323,631,714]" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
12 Postfrons yellow, with small black markings posteriorly; fore femur entirely dark brown; wing markings and contour of vein 2 approximately as in 
<figureCitation box="[628,704,690,714]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[543,578,1000,1022]" captionTargetBox="[219,1300,163,987]" captionTargetId="figure-9@14.[204,1338,151,987]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 21. Bama flavifrons n.sp., holotype female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684889" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684889/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
.................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="McAlpine, 2015" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[1165,1266,690,714]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavifrons" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis box="[1165,1266,690,714]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">flavifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1272,1323,691,714]" pageId="4" pageNumber="28" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[219,1323,727,810]" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="28">—— Postfrons largely black; fore femur yellow on at least basal third; wing markings otherwise; vein 2 usually with more definite and uneven curvature ............................................................................................................... 13</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
<paragraph blockId="4.[219,1323,842,925]" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
13 Penultimate section of vein 4 c. as long as discal crossvein; anterior and discal crossveins enclosed in well separated blackish zones (
<figureCitation box="[385,463,901,925]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[456,491,768,790]" captionTargetBox="[249,1347,164,755]" captionTargetId="figure-10@15.[249,1383,151,755]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 22. Bama ismayi n.sp., holotype female, right wing and adjacent parts." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684891" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684891/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
) .......................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="McAlpine, 2015" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[1196,1266,902,925]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ismayi" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis box="[1196,1266,902,925]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">ismayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1272,1323,901,924]" pageId="4" pageNumber="28" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[219,1323,938,992]" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="28">—— Penultimate section of vein 4 much shorter than discal crossvein; wing markings otherwise ........................................................................................................ 14</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
<paragraph blockId="4.[219,1323,1023,1253]" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
14 Fore femur yellow basally, brown distally; first basal cell with brown to blackish transverse mark (smaller in male) c. halfway between basal and anterior crossveins; second section of vein 4 almost straight; penultimate section of vein 4 not shorter than anterior crossvein; distomedial lobe of mid coxa prominent but broadly rounded, setulose, but without single isolated spinescent bristle (
<figureCitation box="[514,596,1199,1224]" captionStart="Figures 27–29" captionStartId="18.[289,361,1399,1421]" captionTargetBox="[289,1254,151,1383]" captionTargetId="figure-9@18.[289,1254,151,1383]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figures 27–29. Bama bickeli n.sp. (27) Left wing of holotype male. (28) Left wing of female. (29) Mid coxae and adjacent parts of female, anteroventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684897" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684897/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
); male: hind basitarsus broadened, compressed ............................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="McAlpine, 2015" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[1195,1266,1229,1253]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bickeli" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis box="[1195,1266,1229,1253]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">bickeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1272,1323,1229,1252]" pageId="4" pageNumber="28" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[219,1323,1266,1437]" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="28">—— Fore femur entirely yellow; first basal cell with substantial dark mark only at distal extremity; second section of vein 4 slightly curved; penultimate section of vein 4 much shorter than anterior crossvein; distomedial lobe of mid coxa narrowed, setulose, and with one isolated strongly spinescent apical bristle; male: hind basitarsus slender, cylindrical ................................................................................ 15</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
<paragraph blockId="4.[219,1323,1469,1941]" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
15 Point of junction of discal crossvein with vein 4 located on hyaline incision of dark zone (
<figureCitation box="[556,638,1498,1522]" captionStart="Figures 42–44" captionStartId="25.[266,338,1563,1585]" captionTargetBox="[249,1383,151,1545]" captionTargetId="figure-10@25.[249,1383,151,1545]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figures 42–44. Bama monstrans n.sp. (42) Holotype male. (43) Right wing of female. (44) Right hind leg of male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684913" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684913/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">Fig. 43</figureCitation>
); second basal cell with apical bare spot delimited by narrow microtrichose strip; penultimate section of vein 4 more than half as long as anterior crossvein; mid coxa with elongate finger-like distomedial extension lacking marginal ridge (
<figureCitation box="[570,651,1615,1640]" captionStart="Figures 45–47" captionStartId="26.[627,699,1632,1654]" captionTargetBox="[121,1422,178,1743]" captionTargetId="figure-80@26.[121,1421,151,1743]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figures 45–47.Bama monstrans n.sp.(45) Distal part of aedeagus of holotype, right lateral view,scale = 0.3 mm.(46) Preglans from left side, scale = 0.1 mm.(47) Pair of mid coxae of male, left lateroventral view. bu, bulb; fs, flexible section of aedeagus; g, glans; lg, distal lobe of glans; pg, lobe of preglans; st, stipe; tf, terminal filaments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684915" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684915/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
); male: wing with apical dark zone almost as extensive as in female (
<figureCitation box="[713,791,1645,1669]" captionStart="Figures 42–44" captionStartId="25.[266,338,1563,1585]" captionTargetBox="[249,1383,151,1545]" captionTargetId="figure-10@25.[249,1383,151,1545]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figures 42–44. Bama monstrans n.sp. (42) Holotype male. (43) Right wing of female. (44) Right hind leg of male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684913" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684913/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">Fig. 42</figureCitation>
); lobe of preglans with many peg-like spinules (
<figureCitation box="[626,704,1674,1698]" captionStart="Figures 45–47" captionStartId="26.[627,699,1632,1654]" captionTargetBox="[121,1422,178,1743]" captionTargetId="figure-80@26.[121,1421,151,1743]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figures 45–47.Bama monstrans n.sp.(45) Distal part of aedeagus of holotype, right lateral view,scale = 0.3 mm.(46) Preglans from left side, scale = 0.1 mm.(47) Pair of mid coxae of male, left lateroventral view. bu, bulb; fs, flexible section of aedeagus; g, glans; lg, distal lobe of glans; pg, lobe of preglans; st, stipe; tf, terminal filaments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684915" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684915/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
) ................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="McAlpine, 2015" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[1155,1266,1675,1698]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monstrans" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis box="[1155,1266,1675,1698]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">monstrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1272,1323,1675,1698]" pageId="4" pageNumber="28" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[219,1323,1469,1941]" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
—— Point of junction of discal crossvein with vein 4 located within oblique dark band (
<figureCitation box="[594,719,1741,1765]" captionStart="Figures 48–51" captionStartId="27.[167,239,1461,1483]" captionTargetBox="[167,1465,151,1450]" captionTargetId="figure-230@27.[167,1467,151,1450]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figures 48–51. Bama papuanum (Hennig). (48) Right wing of female (holotype of X. papuana). (49) Right wing of male (holotype of X. strigata). (50) Humeral region of right wing of female, showing microtrichia on membrane. (51) Mid coxae of male from right side." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684918" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684918/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">Figs 48, 49</figureCitation>
); second basal cell with solid apical microtrichose zone; penultimate section of vein 4 less than half as long as anterior crossvein; mid coxa with distomedial extension narrow, but less elongate, with sharp marginal ridge extending almost to apex (
<figureCitation box="[756,835,1858,1882]" captionStart="Figures 48–51" captionStartId="27.[167,239,1461,1483]" captionTargetBox="[167,1465,151,1450]" captionTargetId="figure-230@27.[167,1467,151,1450]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figures 48–51. Bama papuanum (Hennig). (48) Right wing of female (holotype of X. papuana). (49) Right wing of male (holotype of X. strigata). (50) Humeral region of right wing of female, showing microtrichia on membrane. (51) Mid coxae of male from right side." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684918" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684918/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
); male: wing with apical dark zone much reduced (
<figureCitation box="[707,786,1887,1912]" captionStart="Figures 48–51" captionStartId="27.[167,239,1461,1483]" captionTargetBox="[167,1465,151,1450]" captionTargetId="figure-230@27.[167,1467,151,1450]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figures 48–51. Bama papuanum (Hennig). (48) Right wing of female (holotype of X. papuana). (49) Right wing of male (holotype of X. strigata). (50) Humeral region of right wing of female, showing microtrichia on membrane. (51) Mid coxae of male from right side." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684918" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684918/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
); lobe of preglans without spinules (
<figureCitation box="[500,578,1917,1941]" captionStart="Figures 52, 53" captionStartId="28.[204,275,1222,1244]" captionTargetBox="[206,1338,208,1196]" captionTargetId="figure-9@28.[204,1338,198,1196]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Figures 52, 53.(52) Bama papuanum (Hennig), distal part of aedeagus.Scale = 0.2 mm.(53) BamashinonagaiMcAlpine, left wing of holotype, male.bu, bulb;g, glans;lg, distal lobe of glans;pg, lobe of preglans;st, stipe;tf, terminal filaments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684920" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684920/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
) ............................................................................ 
